3. * 
<taxonomicName authority="Morong" authorityName="Morong" box="[185,491,160,187]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="alleniana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,394,160,187]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Mimosa alleniana</emphasis>
Morong
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,160,475]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis box="[136,405,196,223]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">J.R.I. Wood et al. 18512</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode box="[420,475,197,223]" country="Bolivia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15532" name="Herbario Nacional de Bolivia, Universidad Mayor de San Andr�s" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">LPB</collectionCode>
, K) is the first record of this species, and of subseries 
<emphasis box="[1079,1236,196,222]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Pedunculosae</emphasis>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[1309,1399,197,222]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1309,1399,197,222]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Mimosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ser. 
<taxonomicName box="[136,226,233,258]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,226,233,258]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Mimosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) for 
<collectingCountry box="[282,368,233,259]" name="Bolivia" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. Given the distribution of the ten known species of subseries 
<emphasis box="[1055,1212,232,258]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Pedunculosae</emphasis>
in campo habitats on hills of the 
<collectingRegion box="[266,342,269,295]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Paraná</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[399,503,269,295]" name="Paraguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<collectingRegion box="[399,503,269,295]" country="Paraguay" name="Asuncion" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Paraguay</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
basins, and of 
<taxonomicName box="[676,821,268,294]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="alleniana">
<emphasis box="[676,821,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">M. alleniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from campo and cerrado in 
<collectingCountry box="[1144,1248,269,295]" name="Paraguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<collectingRegion box="[1144,1248,269,295]" country="Paraguay" name="Asuncion" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Paraguay</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
on the east side of the Rio 
<collectingCountry box="[511,616,305,331]" name="Paraguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<collectingRegion box="[511,616,305,331]" country="Paraguay" name="Asuncion" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Paraguay</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
, this species and subseries could be expected to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[1252,1338,305,331]" name="Bolivia" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. However it is only known in 
<collectingCountry box="[372,454,341,367]" name="Bolivia" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
from a restricted area of very vulnerable 
<emphasis box="[949,1038,340,366]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">cerrado</emphasis>
near Santiago de Chiquitos. It was categorised as Endangered (EN) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mamani, F. &amp; Pozo, P. &amp; Soto, D. &amp; Villarroel, D. &amp; Wood, J. R. I." bookContentInfo="153 pp." box="[544,786,376,403]" journalOrPublisher="Museo de Historia Natural ' Noel Kempff Mercado', Santa Cruz" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Mamani, F., Pozo, P., Soto, D., Villarroel, D. &amp; Wood, J. R. I. (2010) Libro Rojo de las Plantas de los Cerrados del Oriente Boliviano. Museo de Historia Natural ' Noel Kempff Mercado', Santa Cruz, 153 pp." title="Libro Rojo de las Plantas de los Cerrados del Oriente Boliviano" type="book" year="2010">
Mamani 
<emphasis box="[646,703,376,402]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
but this status should be reviewed and perhaps changed to Critically Endangered (CR) as much of its habitat had been cleared and sown with 
<emphasis box="[1047,1282,412,438]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<taxonomicName box="[1047,1170,412,438]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Brachiaria" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">Brachiaria</taxonomicName>
brizantha
</emphasis>
when revisited in 2013.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
